            <main class=""><article class="main-content"><h1 class="">Monticello Montessori Public Charter School</h1>
        <div class="pom-container"></div>
<p class="">Monticello Montessori is a tuition-free, public charter school providing a high-quality Montessori education to children in kindergarten through the eighth grade. Located in Ammon, Idaho, we serve students in Bonneville, Jefferson, and Bingham counties.</p>
        <h2 class="">A Message from Our Administrator</h2>
        <p class=""><img src="https://tb2cdn.schoolwebmasters.com/accnt_404857/site_404858/Graphics/graphic_HomePrincipalPhoto.png" alt="photo of Erica Kemery, Administrator" class="float-right" style="width: 100%; max-width: 150px; display: block;"></p>
<p class="">Dear Families of Monticello Montessori Charter School, </p>
<p class="">As you know, on April 6, the Idaho State Board of Education extended the soft closure for schools through the end of the school year, but asked that all schools continue to teach students from home. This means that Monticello will continue to offer off-campus learning for all our students via online classrooms and learning sites and through email, phone, and other online communications. <br><br></p>
<p class="">We are on a journey together, transitioning from a hands-on learning community focused on healthy relationships to a virtual one. There will no doubt be difficult moments and frustrations, but this is also a wonderful opportunity for families to spend time than before as we slow down and stay home. In our transition, Monticello staff all want to keep focused on our school’s purpose of developing critical thinkers and motivated learners who maximize their inner potentials and experience purpose and meaning in life, take responsibility for their own education, cultivate personal dignity, and develop independence. We hope this will be a time of deep and lasting joy for your family, even in the midst of challenges. <br><br></p>
<p class="">Our goals for our students and families during this soft closure time when we cannot be on campus together is to continue to provide equal educational opportunities for all our students that are individually interesting and challenging. Along with classroom learning, extra support for students in special education and in reading and math tutoring will continue. If your child has not been in touch with his or her teacher or extra support teachers, please contact the office by phone or email right away to double check that we have your most current contact information. <br><br></p>
<p class="">Monticello will continue to be in school until May 28, our last calendar day. We will be holding our annual admission lottery on April 29 in as public a format as possible. Watch for more details on that coming soon. Parent-teacher conferences, calendared for April 23 and 24, will be by phone or email on an as-needed basis, but be sure to contact your child’s teacher any time before or after that for support, clarification, or just to talk things over. Teachers are all working hard while learning these new teaching systems, too, so please be patient with them as they figure out how to make things work as easily as possible for everyone.<br><br></p>
<p class="">Parents, you are so important to our team! Thank you for all you do every day. We are so grateful for you, and we are here to support you in any way we can. We recognize your challenges in work schedules, toddler care, health concerns, elder care, financial strains, social distancing, and supplying simple household needs, in addition to helping children learn at home, and we honor you for all that you are doing, especially the little things that may go by unthanked. You are an overcomer! Be sure to take time to enjoy each of your precious, beautiful children every day. They grow up so fast. <br><br></p>
<p class="">Monticello’s staff is available by phone and email to help. Please don’t hesitate to contact us. <br><br></p>
<p class="">Kind Regards,</p>
	<p class="signature">Erica Kemery</p>
	<p class="">Erica Kemery<br>Administrator</p>
